==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perspicacious
<hw>Per`spi*ca"cious</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r`sp⟦icr⟧*k⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>perspicax</ets>, <ets>-acis</ets>, fr.
<ets>perspicere</ets> to look through: cf. F. <ets>perspicace</ets>. See
<er>Perspective</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the power of seeing
clearly; quick-sighted; sharp of sight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Of acute discernment; keen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Per`spi*ca"cious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Per`spi*ca"cious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perspicacity</ent>⟦br⟧
